description.narrative: Communities and families in priority regions,especially the most disadvantaged women and children, have increased goods and services for sustainable access to clean water and basic sanitation and adopt appropriate hygiene and environmental practices., which contributes to Sanitation, Sanitation (Covid), Water, Water (Covid). UNICEF aims to achieve this through Advocacy And Public Engagement, Developing And Leveraging Resources And Partnerships, Evaluations, Research And Data, Fostering Innovation And Use Of New Technologies, Harnessing Power Of Business And Markets, Operational Support To Programme Delivery, Systems Strengthening And Institution Building, United Nations Working Together. This contributes to the following Country Programme result: Young girls and boys (0â€“5 years), particularly the most deprived and hard-to-reach, are immunized, well nourished, healthy, protected, registered at birth and prepared for school, including in humanitarian situations.
